<!-- Speculative Design Section -->
<section class="section speculative-section" id="speculative">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section-header">
      <h2 class="section-title">Speculative Design</h2>
      <span class="section-subtitle">imagining the future</span>
    </header>

    <div class="speculative-intro">
      <p class="speculative-lead">I imagine the future and implement it.</p>
      <p>I start from a feeling &mdash; a grokking of how life might be when technology really matures &mdash; and start living as if it&rsquo;s already there. I look at where it fails, while focusing on where it excels. I live with new capabilities and imagine what will become possible when millions of people also do.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="speculative-grid">
      <!-- Story 1: The Thinking Room -->
      <article class="speculative-card">
        <div class="speculative-number">01</div>
        <h3 class="speculative-title">The Thinking Room</h3>
        <div class="speculative-body">
          <p>Imagine you are planning your business. You sit in a quiet room. Details keep coming and you voice them without interruption.</p>
          <p>Your agent listens. It doesn&rsquo;t interrupt. But you can ask it anytime: <em>&ldquo;What am I missing? Where are my blind spots? What cognitive biases am I falling into?&rdquo;</em></p>
          <p>When you&rsquo;re done, it gives you back your thinking &mdash; as a presentation, a voice message, a short text, a video. You decide the format.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speculative-output">
          <span class="output-label">Output:</span>
          <span class="output-options">presentation ¬∑ voice memo ¬∑ text ¬∑ video</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Story 2: The Second Opinion -->
      <article class="speculative-card">
        <div class="speculative-number">02</div>
        <h3 class="speculative-title">The Second Opinion</h3>
        <div class="speculative-body">
          <p>Before you share your idea publicly, you stress-test it. The agent plays devil&rsquo;s advocate. It finds the weak points you can&rsquo;t see because you&rsquo;re too close.</p>
          <p>But it also stress-checks your mind. <em>&ldquo;Is this actually a crisis, or am I catastrophizing?&rdquo;</em></p>
          <p>It separates signal from noise when anxiety amplifies everything. Not therapy. Just a reality check from something that doesn&rsquo;t have skin in the game.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speculative-output">
          <span class="output-label">Mode:</span>
          <span class="output-options">devil&rsquo;s advocate ¬∑ anxiety filter ¬∑ reality check</span>
        </div>
      </article>

      <!-- Story 3: The Night Shift -->
      <article class="speculative-card speculative-card-expanded">
        <div class="speculative-number">03</div>
        <h3 class="speculative-title">The Night Shift</h3>
        <div class="speculative-body">
          <p>While you sleep, the system works.</p>

          <div class="night-shift-timeline">
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <span class="timeline-time">22:00</span>
              <span class="timeline-event">Obsidian vault commits to git. Day captured.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <span class="timeline-time">every 15m</span>
              <span class="timeline-event">Chrome history syncs to searchable database.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <span class="timeline-time">09:30</span>
              <span class="timeline-event">Health briefing: sleep duration, HRV, weekly steps.</span>
            </div>
            <div class="timeline-item">
              <span class="timeline-time">10:00</span>
              <span class="timeline-event">Research digest: 10 relevant + 10 serendipitous finds.</span>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="speculative-detail">Today&rsquo;s digest: &ldquo;Measuring AI Ability to Complete Long Tasks&rdquo; from arXiv, &ldquo;Claude Code Best Practices&rdquo; from Medium, &ldquo;LLMs in Scientific Method&rdquo; from Nature. Themes extracted from your recent work.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="speculative-output">
          <span class="output-label">Sources:</span>
          <span class="output-options">arXiv ¬∑ Nature ¬∑ Medium ¬∑ HN ¬∑ Reddit</span>
        </div>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="speculative-note">These aren&rsquo;t concepts. This is the system I use daily.</p>
  </div>
